# Multi-Table Support — Architecture & Implementation Plan

## Problem
The app currently manages a **single** dynamic table (`dynamic_items`). Users can
define custom fields and CRUD items in that one table.  We need to support
**multiple independent tables**, each with its own schema (fields) and data
(items).

## Design Decisions

### 1. Per-Table Physical SQLite Tables
Each logical table gets its own physical SQLite table named `items_{table_id}`
(e.g. `items_1`, `items_2`).

**Why:** Each table keeps its own column namespace — no column-name collisions
between tables.  The existing dual-storage approach (JSON `data` column + real
per-column values for native SQL search/sort) is preserved per table.

### 2. RESTful Nested Routes
All field/item endpoints are scoped under `/api/tables/{table_id}/…`.

**Why:** Clean REST semantics.  Easy to add per-table middleware/auth later.
Frontend URL state can naturally reflect the active table.

### 3. Auto-Migration on Startup
On first startup after upgrade, the backend detects a legacy single-table setup
and auto-creates a "default" table, migrates existing fields/items.

## Database Schema

### New: `dynamic_tables` (metadata)
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS dynamic_tables (
    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    name        TEXT    NOT NULL UNIQUE,         -- machine name (slug)
    label       TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT '',      -- human display name
    created_at  TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);
```

### Modified: `dynamic_fields` (+ table_id FK)
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS dynamic_fields (
    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    table_id    INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES dynamic_tables(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    field_name  TEXT    NOT NULL,
    field_type  TEXT    NOT NULL CHECK(field_type IN ('int','float','text','date','datetime')),
    field_label TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
    field_order INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at  TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),
    UNIQUE(table_id, field_name)
);
```

### Per-table items tables: `items_{table_id}`
Created dynamically when a new table is created:
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS items_{id} (
    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    owner       TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',
    data        TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
    created_at  TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),
    updated_at  TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);
```
Custom field columns are added via `ALTER TABLE items_{id} ADD COLUMN …` and
dropped via `ALTER TABLE items_{id} DROP COLUMN …` (with table-recreation
fallback for older SQLite).

### Legacy migration (one-time, on startup)
```
1. CREATE dynamic_tables IF NOT EXISTS
2. IF dynamic_tables is empty AND dynamic_fields has rows:
   a. INSERT INTO dynamic_tables (name, label) VALUES ('default', 'Default')
   b. ALTER TABLE dynamic_fields ADD COLUMN table_id INTEGER
      DEFAULT <new_table_id>
   c. Recreate dynamic_fields UNIQUE constraint on (table_id, field_name)
   d. ALTER TABLE dynamic_items RENAME TO items_<new_table_id>
   e. All future references use items_{table_id}
```

## API Surface

### Tables — `/api/tables`
| Method   | Path                      | Description           |
|----------|---------------------------|-----------------------|
| `GET`    | `/api/tables`             | List all tables       |
| `POST`   | `/api/tables`             | Create table          |
| `PUT`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}`  | Update table          |
| `DELETE` | `/api/tables/{table_id}`  | Delete table + cascade|

POST body: `{ name: str, label?: str }`

### Fields — `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields`
| Method   | Path                                            | Description               |
|----------|-------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| `GET`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields`                 | List fields for table     |
| `POST`   | `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields`                 | Create field              |
| `PUT`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields/{field_id}`      | Update field              |
| `DELETE` | `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields/{field_id}`      | Delete field              |
| `POST`   | `/api/tables/{table_id}/fields/reorder`         | Reorder fields            |

POST body same as current: `{ field_name, field_type, field_label }`

### Items — `/api/tables/{table_id}/items`
| Method   | Path                                            | Description               |
|----------|-------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| `GET`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}/items`                  | List items (paginated)    |
| `GET`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}/items/{item_id}`        | Get single item           |
| `POST`   | `/api/tables/{table_id}/items`                  | Create item               |
| `PUT`    | `/api/tables/{table_id}/items/{item_id}`        | Update item               |
| `DELETE` | `/api/tables/{table_id}/items/{item_id}`        | Delete item               |

Query params for list unchanged: `?page, page_size, search, sort_by, sort_dir`.
Body for create/update unchanged.

## Frontend Changes

### New Types (`types.ts`)
```ts
interface Table {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  label: string;
  created_at: string;
}
```

### New Components

**`TableSelector.tsx`** — Dropdown/combobox to switch between tables.  Shows
  `table.label` (falls back to `table.name`).  Calls `onTableChange(tableId)`.

**`TableManager.tsx`** — Dialog to create/rename/delete tables.  Renders a list
  of tables with edit (pencil) and delete (trash) actions, plus a "New Table"
  form (name + label).

### Modified Components

**`api.ts`** — Add `listTables`, `createTable`, `updateTable`, `deleteTable`.
  Change all field/item methods to accept `tableId: number` and prefix routes
  with `/api/tables/${tableId}/`.

**`App.tsx`** — Add `currentTableId` state (or `null` before table loads).
  On mount: load tables, auto-select first or "default".  Render
  `<TableSelector>` / `<TableManager>` in the header.  Pass `currentTableId` to
  all child components.  Reload fields + items when `currentTableId` changes.

**`DataTable.tsx`** — Accept `tableId` prop, pass to API calls.  Show
  table name in header.

**`FieldManager.tsx`** — Accept `tableId` prop, pass to API calls.

**`ItemForm.tsx`** — Accept `tableId` prop, pass to API calls.

